<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[264,1323,1797,1904]" lastBlockId="18.[264,1322,284,470]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,392,1797,1823]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Metope with or without intermediate keels. Pronotum with anterior margin strongly convex. Fore wings without hypocostal plate, veins keel-shaped. Radius multifurcate (
<number box="[437,500,1878,1904]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="7.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="2.0">2–12</number>
), median bifurcate, cubitus anterior simple. 
<collectingCountry box="[1100,1159,1878,1904]" name="India" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Hind</collectingCountry>
wings well developed, three-lobed, with deep incision between remigium and vannus, anal lobe narrow, veins with numerous branches apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[264,1322,284,470]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Phallobase with distinct dorso-lateral and ventral lobes. Aedeagus with a pair of ventral hooks and a pair of apical processes. Capitulum of style with distinct apical and lateral teeth.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
